<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.neriak.com/ubb/Forum16/HTML/000003.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#707070"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Sevok Celith'ar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Simply reply to this message, then in the message body list a little info about the quest, then the faction adjustments (both + and -) you get for doing the quest.<P><BR>------------------<BR>Sevok Celith'ar<BR>Teir'dal Necromancer, 30th Rank<BR>Xegony<p>[This message has been edited by Sevok Celith'ar (edited March 14, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Thundarbreath</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Here is an interesting quest for worshippers of Bertoxxulous and is also good if you are trying to improve faction with his followers the Bloodsabers (although a simpler way is to kill brothers chintle and and estle in west karanas or brother nallin in north karanas if you are high enough lvl).  It combines a freeport quest and a qeynos quest. Start in Freeport talk to Lagus Pladeson of the Steel Warriors (he can be found in the Steel Warriors guild near the arena, I think it is the next building over, but dont quote me). If you aren't killed on sight ask "Who is Milea". Tell him "Milea is in East Karana" He gives you a letter to bring to her.  She can be found at the end of the gorge that runs next to the ramp to Highhold in East Karana.  Giving her the letter gives the following faction:  +Steelwarriors,+guards of qeynos, +knights of truth, -corrupt guards of Qeynos, -Freeport Militia.  Now if you Murder Milia after she gets the note you get the following factions: +corrupt guards of qeynos, +freeport militia, -steel warriors, -qeynos guards, -knights of truth.  Basically you have alot of factions canceling each other out and you get some minor experience for each time you complete the quest.  Now, when you kill milea she drops a monogrammed veil...bring it to qeynos catacombs to rithur (I forget his last name...he is straight in from the entrance of plaguebringers guild).  He gives a guest to kill milea...give him the monogrammed veil and get these adjustments...+bloodsabers,+opaldarbryer, +corrupt guards of qeynos, -priests of life,-guards of qeynos.  I usually try to kill a few gnoll pups on my way into town to cancel out the bad faction with the guards im about to get.  If I could raise priests of life faction this would be a nice little experience getter...but i guess bad faction with these do-gooders is part of playing an evil cleric.  There is a fourth way of doing this if you are gonna do a round trip, you can talk to Nerissa Clothspinner in Qeynos, she will give you a message to give to milea.  IF you give Milea the message, you will get some faction adjustments (Im not sure which but they are basically for the "goodie" side. Once you give her the message be sure to kill her quick or a corrupt guard will come and kill her for you and you wont get a chance to get faction for the kill.  Killing the guard that comes to kill her will result in anti-bloodsaber faction adjustments...dont kill this guy if you worship bertoxxulous.  <P>[This message has been edited by Thundarbreath (edited March 24, 2000).]<P>[This message has been edited by Thundarbreath (edited March 24, 2000).]<p>[This message has been edited by Thundarbreath (edited March 24, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
